repository-code: "https://github.com/Benjamin-KY/open-harness-atlas"
url: "https://github.com/Benjamin-KY/open-harness-atlas"
abstract: >-
  open-harness-atlas is a publicly-visible, jurisdiction-neutral
  catalog and knowledge graph of free, open-source harnesses
  (governance, agent, evaluation, red-team, routing) and free
  education resources. It is the technical answer to the
  closed-garden trend in closed-weights model provision — most
  recently the 2026-06-13 Fable / Mythos export-control recall,
  which removed two frontier Anthropic models from worldwide
  access under a US national-security directive within hours.
  Harnesses are the structural scaffolding *around* the model
  that lets operators swap providers, jurisdictions, and weights
  classes without re-architecting the system. This atlas curates
  the open-source layer that makes that swap practical.
